{"year": 1978, "entry_id": "17-split2", "add": true, "presentation_type": "talk", "title": "Interactive Modes of Wolf (Canis lupus) Play.", "authors_raw": "Z. Havkin", "abstract": "Several sources of evidence indicate that play behaviour is a\n                                         well organized phenomenon. Although details of interactions     are\n                                         unique, interactions   as whole composites show a high degree of order.\n                                         In P. Weiss' words: \" ... individual   freedom in the small is compatible\n                                         with the existence of collective    order in the gross ... \".\n\n20.", "parser_format": "split_from_parent_source", "confidence": "manual_split", "qa_flags": ["needs-split-review"], "note_extra": "Split from 17 at: 'Z. Havkin'"}
